Hi Roy,  I guess you didnt read my previous posts.  Let me restate it again....How many votes Maureen gets, does not have any bearing on whether or not she wins the boat.  The winner of the boat is choosen by the staff at WFN.  So you saying "Let's give it to her....let's vote Florida style"....is communicating the wrong message.  It should read....If anyone on the board deserves a shot at the $350 WFN secondary prize package, it's Maureen. Let's give it to her.... let's vote Florida style.  This community has no control over who wins the grand prize boat.  Cheers  FOTB

For those that really want Maureen to win the $350 secondary prize package, you need to disable your acceptance of internet cookies.  by disabling your acceptance of internet cookies, you can vote more the once in a 24 hour period.  In fact you can vote as often as you can point and click a mouse.  In internet explorer, this is how you do it.  1. Click "Tools" 2. Click "Internet Options" 3. Click the "Privacy" Tab 4. Move the sliding bar up all the way until it says "block all cookies"  Then go the the wfn voting site and go nuts.  Vote for Maureen as much as your heart desires.  I have already done this a few times to the tune of some 3000 votes.  If all the folks who are casting votes for Maureen did this, she would be able to crack the top 4 and win the secondary prize.  Cheers,  FOTB

I guess none of you read my previous post in this thread.  I know you are all trying to help Moe climb the ranks in this "Adopt and Angler" online voting contest, but your efforts are rather fruitless.  That is unless each and every one of you voting for Moe, decides to disable their acceptance of "interent cookies" and vote at least a few thousand times a day.  Then Moe may make some progress and move up a few notches in the online voting.  In my opinion....it just isnt worth it to sit in front of your PC and click on the "Vote" button time after time after time.  I calculated that one vote takes about 2 seconds.  That works out to 30 votes a minute and 1800 votes an hour.  If you do this for a few hours (3) each day for the entire duration of the contest, you would have approx 250,000 votes.  Is this all worth a $350.00 BPS/WFN prize package?  That is what the top 4 online vote getters win.  To some entrants obviously, but to me it just is not worth the effort it would take to win one of the 4 secondary prizes.   The Grand Prize Boat/$2000 BPS shopping spree is awarded by WFN....they are the ones who pick the one winner out of all the 400 entries.  Cheers,  FOTB

I have also entered the Adopt an Angler contest and currently sit in 10th place.  I wish Motv8tr all the best in winning the Bass boat, $2000 BPS shopping spree and WFN fishing lessons.  At one point I was in 2nd place, but have quickly dropped out of the top 4.  Just an FYI.  The top 4 online vote getters win the 4 secondary prizes.  The Grand prize winner is chosen by the folks at WFN.  GRAND PRIZE INCLUDES: Brand new 2007 Panfish 17 Tracker Boat with Trailer (retail $15,000 Cdn.) $2,000 Shopping spree to Bass Pro Shops Canada Lessons from WFN Pro Angler  Four (4) secondary prizes will be awarded to the top 4 online entries as voted by you! Secondary prizes include: $250 Gift card to Bass Pro Shops and a WFN prize package.  Please Note:  Several folks who have entered this contest, have discovered a way around the 1 vote/24 hour period limitation.  If you disable the "acceptance of cookies" from within your browser settings, you can vote as many times as you like.  In fact you can sit in front of you PC and keep voting for yourself for hours on end if you want the secondary prize bad enough.  The botton line is....the 4x secondary prizes will be awarded to the Adopt an Angler entrants who have the most time on their hands.  It's amazing what folks will do for a $350 prize package.  Cheers  FOTB
